documents.document:
In the season of snow,
in the immeasurable cold,
we grow cruel but honest;

Now the sea
is in me: I am the fish, the fish
glitters in me;

then they rose, tiny fireworks,
into the leaves
and hovered;

Alone,
in the crown of the tree,
I went to China,
I went to Prague;
I died, and was born in the spring;
I found you, and loved you, again.

I think
of the thickness of the serious woods
around the dark bowls of the Truro ponds;

I think
of the thickness of the serious woods
around the dark bowls of the Truro ponds;
